==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bitt
<hw>Bitt</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Bitts</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To put round the bitts;
<as>as, to bitt the cable, in order to fasten it or to slacken it
gradually, which is called <ex>veering away</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bittacle</ent>⟦br⟧
